{"created": "2026-03-17T07:57:55.857335", "current_version": "1.0.0", "project": "ESP32 Distance Sensor", "versions": {"1.0.0": {"created": "2026-03-17T07:57:55.857333", "creator": {"program": "sphinx_needs", "version": "7.0.0"}, "needs": {"SPEC_LED_ARCH_2": {"acceptance_criteria": "", "api_signature": "", "arch": {}, "avatar": null, "closed_at": null, "completion": null, "component": "", "constraints": [], "constraints_error": null, "constraints_passed": true, "constraints_results": {}, "content": "**Design:** In-memory LED state buffer for performance optimization and atomic updates.\n\n**Implementation:**\n\n- Buffer Structure: Array of ``led_color_t`` structures (3 bytes per LED: R, G, B)\n- Dynamic Allocation: ``malloc()`` during initialization based on configured LED count (REQ_LED_3)\n- State Separation: RAM buffer independent from physical LED state until ``led_show()``\n- Update Pattern: Modify buffer \u2192 call ``led_show()`` \u2192 physical update\n- Memory Management: Allocation during init, deallocation during cleanup\n\n**Validation:** Buffer allocates correctly for configured LED count, updates modify only\nbuffer until show, memory freed on cleanup.", "created_at": null, "docname": "12_design/spec_led_controller", "doctype": ".rst", "duration": null, "external_css": "external_link", "external_url": null, "has_dead_links": false, "has_forbidden_dead_links": false, "header_file": "", "id": "SPEC_LED_ARCH_2", "id_prefix": null, "is_external": false, "is_import": false, "is_modified": false, "jinja_content": false, "layout": null, "lineno": 38, "links": ["REQ_LED_2", "REQ_LED_3"], "links_back": ["SPEC_LED_SIM_1"], "max_amount": null, "max_content_lines": null, "modifications": 0, "parameters": "", "params": null, "parent_need": null, "parent_needs": [], "parent_needs_back": [], "parts": {}, "post_content": null, "post_template": null, "pre_content": null, "pre_template": null, "prefix": null, "priority": "", "query": null, "rationale": "", "returns": ""